cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.LO 

This paper is primarily focused on programming language design and implementation, specifically for low-level concurrent programming. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of modern multi-processor architectures and optimizing compilers, which falls under cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.CR (Hardware Architecture and Design), respectively. The paper also presents a new approach for enforcing memory constraints, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper presents benchmarks for data structures, which could be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
